2);\n        output.writeShort(3);\n        output.writeByte(7);\n        output.writeShort(4);\n        output.writeByte(12);\n        output.writeShort(5);\n        output.writeShort(6);\n        output.writeByte(1);\n        output.writeUTF(\"java/lang/Object\");\n        output.writeByte(1);\n        output.writeUTF(\"<init>\");\n        output.writeByte(1);\n        output.writeUTF(\"()V\");\n        output.writeByte(7);\n        output.writeShort(8);\n        output.writeByte(1);\n        output.writeUTF(internalName);\n        output.writeByte(1);\n        output.writeUTF(\"Code\");\n        output.writeShort(0x0021);\n        output.writeShort(7);\n        output.writeShort(2);\n        output.writeShort(0);\n        output.writeShort(0);\n        output.writeShort(1);\n        output.writeShort(0x0001);\n        output.writeShort(5);\n        output.writeShort(6);\n        output.writeShort(1);\n        output.writeShort(9);\n        output.writeInt(17);\n        output.writeShort(1);\n        output.writeShort(1);\n        output.writeInt(5);\n        output.writeByte(0x2A);\n        output.writeByte(0xB7);\n        output.writeShort(1);\n        output.writeByte(0xB1);\n        output.writeShort(0);\n        output.writeShort(0);\n        output.writeShort(0);\n        output.flush();\n        return bytes.toByteArray();\n    }\n\n    private static void rethrowIfNotNativeImageDynamicClassLoadingError(Error error) {\n        if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n            throw error;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class ByteArrayClassPath extends ClassLoader {\n        private final String resourceName;\n        private final byte[] classBytes;\n\n        private ByteArrayClassPath(String className, byte[] classBytes) {\n            super(null);\n            this.resourceName = className.replace('.', '/') + \".class\";\n            this.classBytes = classBytes.clone();\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public InputStream getResourceAsStream(String name) {\n            if (resourceName.equals(name)) {\n                return new ByteArrayInputStream(classBytes);\n            }\n            return super.getResourceAsStream(name);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class TestingClassLoader extends AbstractClassLoader {"}, {"oldText": "}\n\nclass ReloadedTypeForAbstractClassLoaderFixture {\n}\n", "newText": "}\n"}]}
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating cglib compatibility issues**\n\nI need to fix an error related to ASM version in cglib 3.3, which doesn’t support Java 21 class major 65. I’m considering compiling against a lower target. One option is to use the existing library class compiled in Java 8. I wonder if I could reload a class from the cglib jar itself. But, if I define a transformed class with the same name in my loader, could that break the package seal? I'm checking how to manage the generation and transformation processes too.\n\n**Analyzing native image resource handling**\n\nI'm thinking about how class resources work in a native image context versus a JVM. It seems that for a native image, I might need specific resource metadata for something like \"net/sf/cglib/transform/ClassFilter.class.\" I wonder if including a library class would suffice since the resource metadata can capture class resources. There's a concern if loading ClassFilter via AbstractClassLoader would lead it to conflict with the parent class loader. If defining the class succeeds, I can check its name and loader, but there might be issues with the native image allowing .class resources. So, generating a Java 8 class file resource manually could be an alternative solution.\n\n**Exploring class loading strategies**\n\nI'm considering how to work with binary classes. One option is to write bytes to resources and then have a custom class loader return a ByteArrayInputStream. However, since my call site relies on classPath.getResourceAsStream, which is part of the ClassLoader, I wouldn't need resource metadata here. Alternatively, I could create a custom ClassLoader that overrides getResourceAsStream to return a hardcoded byte array for a generated class with a major version of 52. This approach might work well!\n\n**Considering class loading options**\n\nI'm thinking I don't need to rely on direct reflection after all. I could use the ByteArrayClassPath class loader to override getResourceAsStream. I'll have to import ByteArrayInputStream, InputStream, and IOException for that. It seems I can copy generatedClassBytes without using reflection. The specific class name I need is \"cglib.cglib.ReloadedTypeForAbstractClassLoaderFixture\". So, no extra top-level class is needed, and I’ll remember to remove the class at the bottom.\n\n**Thinking through exceptions**\n\nI’m wondering if I need to have class loading results catch RuntimeExceptions. In native code, does CodeGenerationException wrap an Error? Actually, CodeGenerationException is a RuntimeException from AbstractClassLoader; it’s not for Errors. But I’m pondering whether UnsupportedFeatureError counts as an Error. Then there's the ClassWriter: can it throw TypeNotPresent? Hmm, I think I need to ensure that defined classes on the JVM repeat loads returning the same result.\n\n**Updating test resources**\n\nI see that the LoadedClass line gets hit for the first time but returns null, and then it returns not null on a repeat. That's good information! Now, I need to update the test resources to remove the resources block. It looks like it's time to make some edits to ensure everything functions properly. I'll get started on that update right away!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_095d48dd3c7cec6c0169f697566e2c8192bd8ff63e960fdda4\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9pdwkXQ09w7Kivbj1esyvzHHXv7kAMBPPWSTp_A1e8YlVdi3WF2oOZ4xQ2g3J895aZV_qreDMeG0pnZEbsq7pDlMzjG9_32-fTBuL6r4faaYcOMvFMqVLmVvPiOiNl2Euz2yTFR_f1TL7n_L1kXO1N9eyKoIOOBOpOKEaPyfb3NuTtwPwgzB7kUEnLvITIv8CIyZOB2YxT4KS5QOSaLwbs6_WZsIRlJMkFzdFMAHk32PoF_f_1aViG02OYujcmij7Y_quDhrFc7lXB6sPtgOqr6StADI2pd_iKaSt93_ksDF22NB7am5QNSEVoFuYzdIhQy3e_cQdeHaI5xgIbRVVFtQ_ZIkIhqmgHZr4cMEm0Q5KwhiERbLz3Ku0JrKqYM38oYcsbm6V9qDXlxZGGVF2wP2sGi4dIbMU8gXgVKkp4w3HwCorlKIjFWgoOxlZftf1I1qYFScTuUx-WvELQawBE0coShbhU2BwIC7JnINJucE3V98Tj5Oh6rzOEFStF5Aube5THHbTPH-M12esDw86il-xgKOXU